                           int lexFile,
                           int offset)
Constructor that accepts noun synset properties.

Parameters:
definition - Short description / definition of the meaning.
examples - Examples of how the synset is used.
senseKeys - Keys of word senses associated with this synset.
pointers - Pointers to unresolved relationships.
lexFile - Lexical file that contains the synset.
offset - Byte offset into the data file where synset is defined.

getHypernyms

public NounSynset[] getHypernyms()

Returns the direct hypernyms (superordinate types), if any, of this type.

For example, the hypernym of "tent" is "shelter".

public NounSynset[] getInstanceHypernyms()

Returns the instance hypernyms of this synset. An instance hyponym is a specific instance of something and the instance hypernym represents the reflexive type. For example, the instance hypernym of "Mississippi River" is "river".
